projects.title: Image Captioning & Sentiment Analysis (Web & Mobile)
projects.description: This project was developed as part of a group assignment in the sixth semester, focusing on combining AI with full-stack development. I contributed by gathering and creating datasets of text and images, training the AI model in Python to generate captions and perform sentiment analysis, and integrating the model into an API using Flask for seamless communication. I also developed two application versions: a mobile app with Flutter and a web app with Laravel, ensuring consistent functionality and user experience across platforms. Through this project, I gained valuable skills in AI integration, cross-platform development, and collaborative teamwork.

projects.title: ReactWhatsApp Clone
projects.description: A comprehensive React Native mobile application that clones WhatsApp's interface, developed as a learning project to master mobile development skills. Built with React Native 0.70.0 and modern mobile development practices, this application replicates WhatsApp's core features including chat interface, status updates, call history, and community features. The app features a bottom navigation system with four main tabs (Chat, Status, Community, Calls), real-time chat interface using react-native-gifted-chat with custom bubble styling, comprehensive chat list with avatar, contact names, last messages, and timestamps, call history management, and status/updates functionality. Key technical implementations include React Native navigation system, state management for chat data, custom UI components matching WhatsApp's design system, integration with react-native-vector-icons for consistent iconography, and responsive design for both Android and iOS platforms. This project demonstrates mobile development expertise, UI/UX implementation skills, component architecture, and modern React Native development practices.
projects.shortDescription: WhatsApp clone mobile application with chat interface, status updates, and call history built with React Native
features: Bottom navigation with 4 main tabs (Chat, Status, Community, Calls)

Responsive layout for various screen sizes

projects.title: Info.go.id – PPID Mobile Application Development
projects.description: This project was developed during my internship at Sangkuriang as part of the PPID mobile application initiative. My role focused on converting Figma UI designs into a fully functional mobile application using Flutter, incorporating Bloc state management to ensure smooth performance and maintainable architecture. I also implemented secure login functionality with Recaptcha, strengthening the application’s authentication system. Additionally, I handled API integration between web and mobile platforms to enable seamless connectivity and data synchronization. Through this project, I enhanced my expertise in mobile development, secure authentication, responsive UI design, and effective state management.

projects.title: Portal Nasional Mobile App Maintenance
projects.description: This project was carried out during my internship at Sangkuriang, where I served as a Maintainer for the Portal Nasional mobile application built with React Native. My responsibilities included addressing issues caused by a dead API by replacing non-functional endpoints with dummy data to ensure the app continued running smoothly. I also conducted performance analysis, identified bottlenecks, and applied effective solutions to maintain a seamless user experience. Through this role, I gained practical experience in mobile application troubleshooting, live maintenance, and enhanced my skills in React Native development.
projects.shortDescription: Maintenance of Portal Nasional mobile app built with React Native, focusing on troubleshooting and performance improvements
features: Maintained and updated Portal Nasional mobile application
Replaced dead API endpoints with dummy data
Conducted performance analysis and applied fixes
Troubleshooting and live maintenance
Enhanced reliability and user experience

projects.title: Employee Monitor System
projects.description: A comprehensive web-based employee monitoring and management system developed during my internship challenge program. Built with Laravel 11.x and modern frontend technologies, this system enables companies to efficiently monitor employee attendance, track daily activities, and manage user roles. The application features a multi-role system (Admin, Management, Employee) with role-based access control, real-time attendance tracking with check-in/out functionality, comprehensive activity logging with proof uploads, and analytics dashboard with data export capabilities. Key technical implementations include SQLite database with Eloquent ORM relationships, responsive UI using Tailwind CSS and Alpine.js, authentication system with Laravel Breeze, and advanced filtering with CSV export functionality. This project demonstrates full-stack development skills, database design, user authentication, and modern web development practices.
projects.shortDescription: Multi-role employee monitoring system with attendance tracking, activity logging, and analytics dashboard built with Laravel
features: Multi-role authentication system (Admin, Management, Employee)
Real-time attendance tracking with check-in/check-out functionality
Employee activity logging with proof upload capabilities
Comprehensive user management with role assignment
Analytics dashboard with attendance statistics and charts
Data export functionality (CSV format)
Advanced filtering and search capabilities
Responsive design for desktop and mobile devices
Profile management and settings
Real-time notifications and status updates

projects.title: Rice Disease Classification with Swin Transformer and LLM Recommendations
projects.description:
An innovative agricultural technology solution that bridges the gap between rice disease detection and treatment accessibility. Developed as my final thesis project, this AI-powered mobile application helps farmers quickly identify rice plant diseases and receive appropriate treatment recommendations.

The project combined extensive research in computer vision and natural language processing to create a practical solution for real agricultural challenges. I collaborated directly with farmers and agricultural specialists during the validation phase, ensuring the system meets actual field requirements.

This end-to-end solution demonstrates how modern AI can create tangible value in traditional industries while emphasizing user-centered design principles.
projects.shortDescription: AI-powered agricultural solution combining Swin Transformer image classification (96.72% accuracy) with LLM treatment recommendations for rice disease identification and management.
features: Comparative analysis of 5 deep learning models (ViT, ResNet, EfficientNet, Inception, Swin Transformer)
Achieved 96.72% accuracy and 96.73% F1-Score with Swin Transformer
Optimized LLM for agricultural recommendations
Full-stack system with Flutter frontend, FastAPI backend, PostgreSQL database, and Docker deployment
Validated by end-users with SUS score of 76.43 (Good)
